{
  "text": "where The resulting D(p-2)-brane is localized in \u03b7 and\u1ef9 direction. However since h \u2032\u2032 y\u03bc = h \u2032\u2032 y\u1ef9 = h \u2032\u2032 y\u03b7 = 0 there is no kinetic term for\u1ef9 so that physical interpretation of this configuration is unclear. For that reason we rather restrict ourselves to the case when \u03c4 y = 0. This is natural choice that implies that non-relativistic D(p-1)-brane wraps spatial direction only. In this case we obtain det A \u03b1\u03b2 =h yy \u00c2 \u2032\u1fb1\u03b2 \u03c4\u1fb1 + \u2202\u1fb1\u03b7 These are standard Buscher's rules [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] for components of T-dual metric in absence of NSNS two form. As a result we obtain following action for non-relativistic D(p-2)-brane",
  "correct_citation": {
